FBIS4-5868 "dreas073_a_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Nissan To Build Trucks in U.S. for Canada Sale Nissan To Build Trucks in U.S. for Canada Sale OW1404160194 Tokyo KYODO in English 1529 GMT 14 Apr 94 OW1404160194 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, April 15 KYODO -- A Canadian subsidiary of Nissan Motor Co. will take delivery of U.S.-built pickup trucks from Nissan Motor Manufacturing Corp. U.S.A. (NMMC) late this month, according to Nissan motor officials. It will be the first time Nissan has exported U.S.-built pickup trucks to Canada. NMMC is a U.S. manufacturing arm of the Japanese automaker. Nissan said some 3,300 trucks will be shipped to Canada from NMMC in the business year that started on April 1.
